Oh, to wander through the glade,
Where wildflowers bloom in peace,
And in the harmony of spring,
All burdens seem to cease.

The dappled light, the gentle air,
Embrace both heart and soul,
In nature’s arms, we find our way,
Where spirits rise and roll.

- Dora Carrington
